author: Jeff Deters
title: Royals tab Terrance Gore for 25-man ALDS roster
text:
Royals tab Terrance Gore for 25-man ALDS roster Gomes, Guthrie left off By Jeff Deters jeff.deters@cjonline.com 
KANSAS CITY, Mo. â€” The Kansas City Royals released their 25-man roster for the American League Division Series against the Houston Astros, which starts at 6:37 p.m. Thursday at Kauffman Stadium, and Terrance Gore is on it. 
The speedster, who made a splash late last season and in the playoffs, is one of six outfielders on the roster. The others are Alex Gordon, Lorenzo Cain, Alex Rios, Jarrod Dyson and Paulo Orlando. Veteran outfielder Jonny Gomes did not make the squad. 
Gore appeared in nine games and stole three bases this season with the Royals. 
The roster includes 11 pitchers and six infielders. Chris Young and Kris Medlen are in, but Jeremy Guthrie is out. Christian Colon is the backup infielder.
